title: NLPCloud client integration
body:
lots of kwargs! generation docs here: https://docs.nlpcloud.com/#generation

This somewhat breaks the paradigm introduced in LLM base class as the stop sequence isn't a list, and should rightfully be introduced at the time of initialization of the class, along with the other kwargs that depend on its presence (e.g. remove_end_sequence, etc.) curious if you'd want to refactor LLM base class to take out stop as a specific named kwarg?

title: [RFC] Self-consistent Draft
body:
Major changes:
- Expose a "generate" method to permit sampling / n-best list generation
- Expose ability to return logprobs of the generated tokens. Add to cohere and OpenAI llms
- Add example prompts from paper https://arxiv.org/pdf/2203.11171.pdf
- Add self-consistent chain-of-thought prompt logic to a chain

I don't like a lot of the overloading int he chain I made so will clean things up. Pubbing for initial feedbak
